rComments: She invited a lot of lawyers to give lectures in their own respected fields. Most of the classes are taught by guest lecturers. However, she is presented in every class and genuinely cares for her students.

She is quite a good teacher - she always explained everything clearly and really cared that the students understood. The grading scheme seemed random and unfair to me since she chose to set the class average for all evaluations at a B, which I thought negatively impacted me academically. Also, don't bother trying to dispute marks.
Best Prof. I ever had! She is so smart and cares that we learn. I wish she taught more classes. She can teach other teachers how to teach.
BEST PROF AT UOFT. Really cares about students and their careers. Tests are extremely fair, if you come to class and do the work you will do good.

BEST law prof available. she cares about your learning experience and reinforces complex ideas with several examples. she's always on time to lecture and teaches you some law tricks to help understand and apply the concepts.
